parameters.name: DAY
parameters.description:
Integer day of year (DAY=1 on
  January 1).

parameters.name: COR
parameters.description:
Integer indicator of the spacecraft
                        orientation correction (1 =
                        correction occurred;  0 =  no
                        correction occurred).

parameters.name: DRATLW
parameters.description:
Daily averaged count rates for the
                        long wavelength channel of the UV
                        photometer.

parameters.name: DRATSW
parameters.description:
Daily averaged count rates for the
                        short wavelength channel of the
                        UV photometer.

parameters.name: HRADSP
parameters.description:
Radial distance of the spacecraft
                        from the Sun's center.

parameters.name: CLATSP
parameters.description:
The celestial latitude of the
                        pointing direction for the
                        spacecraft's +Z axis, where the
                        latter is along the spacecraft spin
                        axis pointed approximately towards
                        the Earth.  The UV photometer
                        points away from the Earth at an
                        angle of 20 degrees to the -Z axis.

parameters.name: CLONSP
parameters.description:
The celestial longitude of the
                        pointing direction for the
                        spacecraft's +Z axis, where the
                        latter is along the spacecraft spin
                        axis pointed approximately towards
                        the Earth.  The UV photometer
                        points away from the Earth at an
                        angle of 20 degrees to the -Z axis.

parameters.name: CLATSU
parameters.description:
The celestial latitude of the Sun as
                        seen from the spacecraft.

parameters.name: CLONSU
parameters.description:
The celestial longitude of the Sun
                        as seen from the spacecraft.

parameters.name: CLATEA
parameters.description:
The celestial latitude of the Earth
                        as seen from the spacecraft.

parameters.name: CLONEA
parameters.description:
The celestial longitude of the Earth
                        as seen from the spacecraft.
